    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-26T02:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-26T02:41:00-05:00" n="590"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-26T16:41:00+09:00">26
                            September 1951—4:41 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>ZX–39742. Fol rel to press simultaneously Tokyo and <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1"
                        >CINCUNC</gloss> Adv 1700 local this date: The United Nations Command
                    liaison officers met with the Communist liaison officers at Kaesong at 1000
                    hours today. The Communist liaison officers proposed a meeting of the delegates
                    at 1000 hours 27 Sep, which proposal was answered by the United Nations Command
                    liaison officers that their instructions were to meet with Communist liaison
                    officers to discuss conditions mutually satisfactory prior to the resumption of
                    conference discussions by the delegations.</p>
                <p>The meeting of the liaison officers was recessed by mutual agreement at 1120
                    hours.</p>
            </div>
